<HEADLINE> Mid-Autumn Celebration Held for Taiwanese in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 Taiwan people
gathered in Beijing today to celebrate the upcoming Mid-Autumn
Festival on September 16, a traditional Chinese holiday.
</P>
<P>
At the event, Wan Guoquan, Vice-Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, extended his best wishes to the 21 million Taiwan
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
"Good relations across the Taiwan Strait will greatly benefit
people on both sides, and Hong Kong's smooth return to the
motherland and the successful practice of the concept "one
country, two systems" will surely contribute to China's final
reunification," Wan said.
</P>
<P>
He added that more Taiwan businessmen are welcome to invest on
the mainland and economic cooperation should be further expanded.
</P>
<P>
"Patriots on Taiwan island have made unremitting efforts to
improve the relations across the strait, as well as to China's
reunification and national rejuvenation," said Wan. He hoped they
will continue their efforts.
</P>
<P>
Performances were staged at the gathering, which was also
attended by Cheng Siyuan, vice-chairman of the National People's
Congress Standing Committee, and Chen Yunlin, director of the
Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
