<HEADLINE> Ghana Reaches Quarters at Under-17 World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARIO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Awule Quaye scored in the 13th
minute, pacing Ghana to a 2-0 victory over Costa Rica and putting
the defending champion in the quarterfinals of the Under-17 World
Cup in Alexandria, Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Michael Coffie added a second goal in the 60th minute and Ghana
finished atop Group D, just ahead of Argentina on goal difference.
</P>
<P>
The victory put Ghana in a round-of-eight meeting with the
runner-up from Group C, either Brazil or Oman.
</P>
<P>
Those two countries face off on Thursday with Ghana getting the
loser and Argentina facing the winner.
</P>
<P>
Ghana's lackadaisical approach cost it several more potential
goals, apparently secure in the knowledge that it already had
guaranteed itself a spot in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
