<HEADLINE> Argentina Reaches Under-17 Soccer Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Argentina beat Bahrain 2-0 to
reach the quarterfinals of Under-17 World Cup in Port Said, Egypt
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Argentina finished second in Group D, sending
it to a round-of-eight meeting with the Group C winner, likely to
be arch-rival Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Ghana beat Costa Rica 2-0 in a game played simultaneously in
Alexandria, giving it the group title on goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Argentina launched a series of attacks on Bahrain's penalty
area and opened the scoring in the 42nd minute thanks to Julio
Javier. Mauro Marchano scored the second in the 72nd to seal the
win. 
</P>
