<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oilfield Discovered in Bohai Sea of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Bohai Oil Company has
announced the discovery of the Bohai Sea's third-largest oilfield,
Nanbao 35-2.
</P>
<P>
The new oilfield, 20 km south of the Jingtang Port in Tangshan,
north China's Hebei province, was found in the central region of
the Bohai Sea, 20 meters underwater, with a structural area of 50
sq km..
</P>
<P>
The Bohai Oil Company has sunk three high-yield wells in the
area since last June and discovered a total of 113 million tons of
geological oil reserves.
</P>
<P>
Nanbao 35-2, the third-largest oilfield found in the region
following Suizhong 36-1, Qinhuangdao 32-6, will produce two
million tons of crude oil per year.
</P>
<P>
The discovery has brought the total oil reserves in the Bohai
Sea from 800 million tons two years ago to the current 1.2 billion
tons, said experts with the Bohai Oil Company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
