<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Visits School On Teachers' Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
expressed his good wishes to the teachers at the Balizhuang
Primary School in Beijing's Haidian District celebrating the 13th
Teachers' Day, which falls today.
</P>
<P>
Li praised the school staff for their efforts to improve
educational quality and conditions and hoped that they will
continue to work hard.
</P>
<P>
Li said that educational departments should give full play to
the role of primary and middle schools' teachers and headmasters
in upgrading students' quality through education.
</P>
<P>
"The demand on headmasters and teachers is heavier when we want
to raise a generation of students with higher quality," Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Breakthroughs should be made in the change of educational
concepts and methods, Li said, asking teachers to improve
themselves so as to meet the need for the 21st century.  
