<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Promotes Economic Ties With Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Industry and Commerce
Minister Nathan Shmuyarira will lead a trade and investment
delegation to Kuwait and Dubai next month in order to strengthen
the economic ties with the Mideast countries.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry said in a statement today that the trade mission
scheduled from October 24 to 30 is aimed at encouraging
Zimbabwean companies to tap the vast potential markets in the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
''Kuwait and Dubai are potential markets for Zimbabwean
products, and local companies are urged to use this opportunity
to identify possible joint venture partners,'' said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe and Kuwait recently signed an economic and technical
cooperation agreement set to increase trade relations between the
two countries, as well as contribute to the process of
strengthening the two countries' respective scientific and
economic bases.
</P>
<P>
Trade relations between Zimbabwe and Kuwait have been growing
steadily over the years, but slackened due to the 1990/91 Gulf
War.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the countries would now continue to build on
this relationship by exchanging trade and investment missions and
other activities which would give greater economic substance to
their cordial political relations. 
</P>
