<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Tobacco Company Donates for Chinese Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Tobacco Company
donated 30 million yuan to the Beijing-based University of
International Business and Economics today, the national Teachers'
Day in China.
</P>
<P>
A special education development fund, named after Ho Ying Jie,
chairman of the board of the company, and general manager Charles
Ho, will be established for the more than 40-year-old university.
</P>
<P>
The Ho family has so far donated more than 600 million yuan for
China's disaster relief and public facilities construction.
</P>
<P>
Wulan Mulun, deputy director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong
Kong Branch, and Li Guohua, vice minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation, were present at the donation ceremony on
the campus today.  
