<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Host International Maritime Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus will host a major
international maritime conference next month, with the theme "a
new era in shipping," a Cypriot shipping official announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
The conference, "Maritime Cyprus 1997 Conference", will be
held on October 6-9, according to Sergios Sergiou, Director of the
Department of Merchant Shipping.
</P>
<P>
It is organized by the Ministry of Communications and Works,
the Ministry of Finance, the Central Bank of Cyprus and the Cyprus
Shipping Council, he said.
</P>
<P>
Among more than 1,000 participants of the conference are
ship owners, brokers, managers, lawyers, accountants,
underwriters and insurers.
</P>
<P>
The participants will have the opportunity to be informed on
the latest developments in international shipping, exchange
views, and even proceed with transactions.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Bank of Cyprus, the island's revenues
from its merchant shipping reaches 50 million Cyprus pounds (about
94 million U.S. dollars) a year, while around 2,000 people are
employed in shipping companies.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus ranks fifth on the list of the world merchant shipping
powers, with 2,640 ships under Cyprus' flag and 24.5 million of
gross tonnage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
