<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot local
industrialists were urged today to upgrade the quality of their
products and services while reducing production cost and finding
new markets to face international competition.
</P>
<P>
The call was made this evening by Minister of Commerce,
Industry and Tourism Kyriakos Christofi in his speech at an
annual general meeting of the Nicosia Chamber of Commerce and
Industry.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that export of local goods in 1996 dropped
by 4.3 percent, while total imports, mainly raw materials and
consumer goods, increased by 11.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
