<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Statistics About Women in Politics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are statistics
boxes about women's role in politics based on latest figures
issued today by the Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) on the eve of
IPU's 98th conference.
</P>
<P>
Women's Suffrage: An abbreviated chronology of the recognition
of women's rights to vote and to stand for election:
</P>
<P>
1788 -- United States (to stand for election)
</P>
<P>
1893 -- New Zealand (to vote)
</P>
<P>
1902 -- Australia (rights subject to conditions or limited)
</P>
<P>
1906 -- Finland
</P>
<P>
1989 -- Namibia
</P>
<P>
1990 -- Samoa
</P>
<P>
1994 -- Kazakstan, Republic of Moldova, South Africa
</P>
<P>
1997 -- United Arab Emirates
</P>
<P>
Women in Parliament: In 50 years, the number of sovereign
states with a parliament increased sevenfold while the percentage
of women MPs worldwide increased fourfold.
</P>
<P>
1945 -- 26 parliaments, 3.0% women MPs, 2.2 percent
</P>
<P>
women senators.
</P>
<P>
1995 -- 176 Parliaments, 11.6 % women MPs, 9.4 percent
</P>
<P>
women senators.
</P>
<P>
Situation at 1 September 1997: 4,555 women MPs across world,
</P>
<P>
 world average: 12.2% percent women MPs
</P>
<P>
Regional Classification on September 1, 1997. (Both Houses)
</P>
<P>
1 Nordic Countries: 36.4%
</P>
<P>
2 Pacific: 13.6%
</P>
<P>
3 Asia: 13.3%
</P>
<P>
4 Europe-OSCE (incl. Nordic Countries): 13.2%
</P>
<P>
5 Americas: 13.1%
</P>
<P>
6 Europe-OSCE (excl. Nordic Countries): 11.5%
</P>
<P>
7 Sub-Saharan Africa: 10.9%
</P>
<P>
8 Arab States: 3.6%
</P>
<P>
National Classification on September 1, 1997. (Both Houses)
</P>
<P>
1 Sweden: 40.4 %
</P>
<P>
2 Norway: 39.4%
</P>
<P>
3 Finland:33.5%
</P>
<P>
4 Denmark: 33%
</P>
<P>
5 Netherlands: 31.3% (Lower House), 22.7% (Upper House)
</P>
<P>
In 51 years of world parliamentary history, only 38 of the 186
states with a legislative institution have, at one time or anther
of their history, selected a woman to preside over Parliament or a
House of Parliament: this has occurred 71 times in all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
