<HEADLINE> Iran Found Buying Arms Parts in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The German Criminal Customs
Office said in Colgone today that Iran had been illegally buying
components from German firms for the manufacture of arms.
</P>
<P>
German law bans arms exports to countries at war or
international trouble spots. According to a Zollkriminalamt (ZKA)
spokesman, Iranians have been buying components in various
countries for assembly at home.
</P>
<P>
ZKA said that more than 10 investigations were going on of the
deals between Iran and German companies. It added that the deals
were thought to have been organized by a Duesseldorf branch of the
Iranian armed forces' Defense Industries Organization.
</P>
<P>
ZKA has found that German firms have mainly exported to Iran
products that could be used for both civilian and military
purposes, while in some cases, however, components clearly
designed for the manufacture of arms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
