<HEADLINE> Closure Causes More Economic Losses to Palestine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Israel's closure has caused
more economic losses to the Palestinian people and Palestinian
businessmen urged Israel to end the closure as soon as possible,
JMCC, an East Jerusalem-based Palestinian news center reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a statement from the Ministry of Agriculture
of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) as saying that daily
losses of the agricultural sector in the West Bank and Gaza Strip
reached 630,000 U.S. dollars due to the closure.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in the West Bank can not market their agricultural
products and those farmers who borrowed loans could not pay back
the money due to the losses of income, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, business sector in the West Bank city of Nablus
also experienced huge losses due to the closure, JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 4,000 business organizations and institutions
registered with the local chamber of commerce have stopped their
operations. Factories in the city are unable to get raw materials
and thousands of workers can not go to work while doctors and
nurses and health workers can not reach their working places
because of the closure, according to JMCC.
</P>
<P>
The businessmen in the city voiced their concern over the
closure and urged international community to pressure Israel to
end the closure as soon as possible, JMCC added.
</P>
<P>
Israel imposed total closure on PNA areas on September 4
following the bombing blasts in Jerusalem, which killed eight
people and injured more than 190 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
