<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamas Spokesman Arrested for Endangering Jordan's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Jordan said today the reason
for arresting the Amman-based Hamas spokesman is that he had made
statements undermining the Kingdoms national security.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Jordan has made public the charge on
Ibrahim Ghosheh who was arrested on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Explaining the reason of the arrest, Jordanian Minister of
State for Information Affairs Samir Mutawe said Ghosheh was
detained for questioning 24 hours after he had given Reuters
Television a statement saying that the "armed struggle against
Israel will continue...as long as the detention of Palestinian
prisoners continue."
</P>
<P>
Mutawe was quoted in Radio Jordan as denying the Monday
accusation by Jordan's opposition parties that the detention "is a
response to American pressure calling to combat terrorism as the
(U.S.) Secretary of State (Madeleine Albright) starts her visit to
the region."
</P>
<P>
The 61-year-old, Jerusalem-born Ghosheh is one of the founders
of the Muslim Brotherhood Movement in Palestine, a member of the
politburo of the Islamic Resistance Movement Hamas and the Hamas
spokesman in Amman.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested following two suicide bombing incidents in
Jerusalem on July 30 and September 4, killing a total of 22
people. The Izzedin Qassam Brigades, the military wing of Hamas
has claimed responsibility for both. Israel has pressured the
Palestinian side to crack down on terrorism
</P>
<P>
Hamas was established in 1987 to fight against Israel's
occupation of Palestine, but the Izzedin Qassam Brigades were
formed in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, a major player in the peace process and having a peace
treaty with the Jewish state, has denounced the bombings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
