<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Journalists Urges to Fight AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAT ES SALAAM, September 10 (Xinhua)-- Tanzanian journalists
today called on all countrymen, irrespective of their religious
beliefs, political affiliations and cultural norms, to unite to
fight the disease of AIDS.
</P>
<P>
At the end of a two-day workshop for heads of mass media on
HIV/AIDS in the Tanzanian capital, the journalists noted that
there should be a consistence and uniformity on messages and
speeches being made on ways to prevent further spread of the
fatal disease.
</P>
<P>
There are three weapons against AIDS, namely, to abstain from
sex, have one regular sexual partner or use condom, according to
the National AIDS Control Program (NACP).
</P>
<P>
Participants of the workshop observed that contradicting
statements among sections of the society who want to safeguard
their interests have placed people in cross roads, hence stalling
efforts being made to save mankind from the deadly disease.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania is said to be leading in Africa with high number of
HIV/AIDS victims. As of last December, there were 88,667 reported
cases in the country, the number which the NACP estimates to
represent only 20 percent of the real number. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
