<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Investment in Central, Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China's new investment
policies have been accepted by Chinese and foreign investors, and
helped bring in more overseas capital for the country's
central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
At the ongoing '97 China Investment and Trade Talks here,
investors from various countries and regions showed great interest
in more than 10,000 projects, put up for negotiations by 26
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions of China.
</P>
<P>
The central and western provinces and regions, such as
Xinjiang, Qinghai and Shaanxi, also presented their own projects,
covering farming, animal husbandry, hi-tech and light industry.
</P>
<P>
There are rich natural and agricultural resources in those
areas, said Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Some provinces in central and western China, such as Shaanxi,
have many science and technology institutes and experts,
indicating great development potential.
</P>
<P>
To encourage more investment in the central and western areas,
China has issued a series of preferential policies, including a
transfer payment plan.
</P>
<P>
The central government has also increased loans to those areas.
According to Sun, about 60 percent of foreign loans have been
granted to central and western China in recent years. Priority is
given to projects concerning transportation, energy and raw
materials.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, China has widened the market in that region,
especially to investment projects which will fully use its local
resource and labor advantages.
</P>
<P>
Those projects, which are limited in eastern China, can be
developed freely in central and western China, and products made
in that region can be sold locally without limits.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, China's central and western areas share only 10
percent of the total investment in China, experts said.
</P>
<P>
In order to narrow the investment gap between eastern and
central and western areas, more needs to be done to improve
the investment environment in those places.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
