<HEADLINE> Telephone Conference on Coal-Mining Safety Held in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua)-- The Ministry of Coal Industry
held a national telephone conference here today to discuss
coal-mining safety and the achievements and problems in the field.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Vice-Minister Wang Xianzheng urged coal mine
operators to pay more attention to safety so as to ensure smooth
production.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August, 57 mining administrations in China had
reached the safety targets set by the ministry, accounting for 59
percent of the total number of state-owned coal mines in the
country.
</P>
<P>
No casulties had occurred in 18 of the 57 mining
administrations in the period, according to the vice-minister.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that many coal mines had invested heavily in
installing safety equipment, and had improved their ventilation
systems. However, the official admitted, some problems remain.
</P>
<P>
Wang asked the key mines to do everything possible to prevent
fatal accidents, and to reduce the number of minor accidents.
</P>
<P>
