<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councilor Meets Australian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Ismail Amat
today told visiting Australian Minister for Immigration and
Multicultural Affairs Philip Ruddock that it is important for the
two countries to cooperate on the ethnic issue.
</P>
<P>
Ismail Amat, the minister in charge of the State Ethnic Affairs
Commission, said that the ethnic issue is a worldwide one, and
that every nation has the right to decide policies and solutions
for its own ethnic matters.
</P>
<P>
He noted that although the two countries have different
cultural backgrounds and social systems, both of them are nations
with multi-ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The Australian friends are welcome to visit areas inhabited by
Chinese minority ethnic groups so as to enhance mutual
understanding, Amat said. He hopes that good bilateral
cooperation between departments for ethnic affairs will be further
developed.
</P>
<P>
Ruddock said that his trip to China has deeply impressed him,
and that sound cooperation between relevant departments of the two
countries will help promote the Sino-Australian relationship
in the future.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Minister in charge of the State Ethnic Affairs
Commission Wen Jing held working talks with the Australian
visitors on Wednesday. The Australian guests will travel to
Xi'an, Shanghai and Guangzhou.  
