<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress Spokesman Gives First Press Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) is a major event which people
all over the country have been following with close attention,
said Party congress spokesman Xu Guangchun in his first press
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The congress, scheduled to open tomorrow, was expected to
deepen political restructuring and make a new breakthrough in
economic restructuring, Xu said at the conference attended
by over 600 Chinese and overseas reporters.
</P>
<P>
Earnest efforts were urged to promote the socialist ethic and
cultural progress, Xu said when asked about what the Chinese
people are expecting from the congress.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question on the shareholding system by a Hong
Kong reporter, Xu said that the system should not be simply
labeled as "privatization." "This is entirely a misunderstanding.
The key lies in who controls the shares," Xu added, saying that
the system is a form of capital organization.
</P>
<P>
Xu expressed his belief that the experience of state-owned
businesses over the past years will be summed up at the congress,
and new decisions will be made, opening up a new situation for the
reform and development of the state businesses.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the political restructuring, Xu said much has been
achieved in this regard since the convening of the 14th National
Party Congress, and added that the political restructuring is sure
to continue along with the deepening of the economic restructuring
and the cross-century development in the country's socialist
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He said that "the building of socialist democracy is our firm
goal."
</P>
<P>
On fighting corruption, Xu said that the fight against corruption
is a long-term task which needs persistent efforts, owing to the
"complicated nature of corruption."
</P>
<P>
"Intensifying our democratic supervision is a key measure to
overcome corruption, and we will never simply copy Western
political system," Xu stressed.
</P>
<P>
The press conference lasted for about an hour.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
