<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Plans to Double Sugar Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam plans to double its
annual sugar production to nearly 1.5 million tons by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
To meet the target, the country should have in operation a
total of 51 sugar mills with a daily capacity to process 97,100
tons of sugarcane, Vietnam News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
There are now 24 sugar mills with a combined annual processing
capacity of 316,000 tons of sugarcane in Vietnam. They put out
520,000 tons of sugar per year, which means a remarkable hike of
per-capita output of seven kilograms this year against 4.3
kilograms in 1994.
</P>
<P>
In the 1997-1998 crop, 13 more sugar mills will stars
operations, and 14 others will be completed by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The fund needed for expanding sugarcane acreage and building
new sugar mills is estimated at 1.2 to 1.3 billion U.S. dollars,
the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Former UN Secretary-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng and
former UN Secretary-General Boutros Boutros Ghali stressed the
importance of cooperation among the developing countries during a
meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
Ghali is visiting China at the invitation of the United Nations
Association of China. He also traveled to the city of Dalian in
northeast China's Liaoning Province, to attend an international
fashion festival.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China places great emphasis on reinforcing its
solidarity and cooperation with other developing countries
including those in Africa, with a view to safeguarding their
rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China advocates the development of friendly
relations with all the countries based on the principle of
mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit, and non-interference
in each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The premier emphasized that all the countries, big or small, rich
or poor, strong or weak, should be equal, and all world issues
should be settled through consultations of people from all
the countries.
</P>
<P>
The world is now marching towards multi-polarization, and this
prominent feature of the present situation in the world is
beneficial to the great cause of peace and development, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The premier also expressed appreciation for Ghali's efforts in
safeguarding world peace and promoting economic development during
his term.
</P>
<P>
Ghali said that the present north-south relations are
complicated, and the developed countries should help the
developing countries develop economy, adding that cooperation
among the third world countries should also be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Ghali spoke highly of China's achievements in its reform and
opening-up efforts, and extended congratulations on the convening
of the 15th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party,
which opens Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
