<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host Intl Epidemiology Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The National Social Security
Authority (NSSA) of Zimbabwe will host a two-day international
symposium on epidemiology occupational health here this month.
</P>
<P>
The symposium will provide a platform for the most recent
scientific advances in occupational health, including health
risks in mining and agriculture, reproductive health risks
associated with work and respiratory diseases.
</P>
<P>
With the theme ''Risk Reduction in the Work Place'', the
symposium, which is being held for the first time in Africa, will
also focus on health effects of pesticides and other chemical
exposures and HIV/AIDS management at work places.
</P>
<P>
Mathew Ncube, NSSA health and safety director, said today in a
statement pre-conference courses for the symposium were held in
South Africa this month.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''there will also be parallel pre-post conference
workshops in Harare and Johannesburg respectively and most
delegates will be scientists who have carried out research on
occupational diseases.''
</P>
<P>
The conference will start on September 17 and it will be
hosted in conjunction with Zimbabwe Occupational Safety Health
Council.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 delegates are expected to attend the conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
