<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Summer Peak For China's Railways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China's Trains carried 162
million people in July and August, up 3.1 percent from the same
period last year, according to a recent report from the
Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
Just over 41 million were long-distance travellers, 26.5
percent more than for the previous 62-day period, which is usually
the peak passenger period, when large numbers of college students
go home for the summer vacation. Also, since the country began the
five-day workweek in May of last year, the number of tourists has
increased.
</P>
<P>
To ease the transportation pressures, the ministry added 260
temporary trains for the two-month period, 178 more than for the
same 1996 period. There are also 160 more short-distance temporary
trains, and 14 tourist trains that cater to foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
And in spite of high temperatures, heavy rains and frequent
flooding, the Ministry was able to see to the safety of all
travelers during that period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
