<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria, Argentina, Colombia
and Paraguay have won next year's World Cup finals after Wednesday
night's competition, taking the number of qualifiers to 13 on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
A total of 32 nations will take part in the finals being staged
from June 10 to July 12 next summer.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria beat Russia 1-0 in Sofia to clinch first place in
European qualifying group two, while Argentina, Colombia and
Paraguay earned the berths by filling the top three places in the
South American qualifying league.
</P>
<P>
Argentina beat Chile 2-1 in Santiago, Colombia beat Venezuela
1-0 in Bogota and Paraguay beat Bolivia 2-1 in Asuncion.
</P>
<P>
The remaining South American qualifier will de decided next
month with Peru, Chile, Bolivia and Uruguay still in contention of
finishing fourth. 
