<HEADLINE> Eco-Internet Leads in Outdoor Quest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XICHANG, Sichuan Province, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Team
Eco-Internet led the first day's competition at the Mild Seven
Outdoor Quest in Xichang, China's Sichuan province, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Eco-Internet clocked four hours 31 minutes and 50 seconds
for the win. Photon Red Bull finished second in 4:38:53 and Team
SCAR came third in 4:40:10.
</P>
<P>
The Mild Seven Outdoor Quest, a grueling challenge, consists
of trail running, mountain biking, offroad inline skating, river
paddling, lake paddling, mountain bike biathlon, and
mountaineering. Each team includes at least one woman.
</P>
<P>
Competitors will carry all their own food and water. If a
teammate is out by injury or broken will, the entire team will be
disqualified. Lowest overall time at the end of four days is the
winner. 
</P>
