<HEADLINE> 3 Killed by Extremists in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Three farmers were killed and
one seriously wounded today in an attack by suspected Muslim
extremists in a southern Philippine province.
</P>
<P>
The four victims and their two companions were on way to their
farm in Basilan Province when they were chanced upon by 10
heavily-armed men, according to the Philippine News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The armed men sprayed the six farmers with automatic gunfire,
killing three and wounding one. But two others managed to hide and
escape from the carnage.
</P>
<P>
The provincial police authorities have sent a team to track
down the killers, who were believed to be members of the Muslim
extremist Abu Sayyaf group.  
</P>
