<HEADLINE> HK to Host International Investment Funds Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Investment
Funds Association (HKIFA) will host the 11th International
Investment Funds Conference in October, it was announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Peter Lord, the newly-appointed
 HKIFA chairman, said this conference will bring together industry
 leaders from about 30 countries to discuss industry developments
and matters of common interest.
</P>
<P>
After three days in Hong Kong, the delegates will travel to
Beijing where China's central bank, the People's Bank of China,
will co-host another day of meetings.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first occasion that the conference is to be held
in Asia outside Japan, and is a recognition of the growth,
maturity and importance of the Hong Kong fund management
industry," said Lord, who is also managing director of LGT Asset
Management Ltd.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that currently more than 100 billion
U.S. dollars is managed by HKIFA member companies in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Lord said that in the coming year, a number of initiatives will
 be undertaken on the educational front, targeting both at
industry participants and at the general public.
</P>
<P>
For industry participants, HKIFA endeavors to increase the
depth and scope of the pensions and unit trust training courses.
</P>
<P>
These programs aim at enabling existing and potential industry
participants to have a thorough understanding of the operation of
the industry, with the ultimate objective of further boosting the
professional standards of the industry.
</P>
<P>
In addition to organizing training for industry participants in
 Hong Kong, the HKIFA also runs programs for Chinese mainland
regulators.
</P>
<P>
"We note that a top priority for the mainland authorities is to
 establish the regulatory framework for the fund industry and we
hope that we can, through this training, facilitate this process
by sharing with them our international experience and expertise,"
said Lord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
