<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loans to Pakistan, Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
said today it has approved 60 million U.S. dollars in loans to
help Pakistan and Sri Lanka improve their science education.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will get a 40-million-dollar loan to fund its Second
Science Education Sector Project, which will provide science
laboratories and equipment, textbooks, computers and teacher
training to 2,000 schools in the country.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka will receive a 20-million-dollar loan to finance its
Science and Technology Personnel Development Project, the
Manila-based bank said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The project will boost industrial productivity and promote a
stronger partnership between private industry and science and
technology institutes and research and development centers, the
bank said.
</P>
<P>
Both loans are interest-free and carry a service charge of 1
percent. 
