<HEADLINE> Abacha Appears Healthy, Says Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Head of State
General Sani Abacha appeared in public Wednesday in the capital
Abuja, dousing speculations that he is seriously ill.
</P>
<P>
According to This Day, one of the leading national newspapers,
Abacha arrived at the venue for the 27th yearly Accountants'
Conference of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria
(ICAN), looking healthy, although he appeared slimmer than usual.
</P>
<P>
He spent one and a half hours at the meeting and took the
salute standing from the very beginning to the end of the event
as usual, without showing any clear sign of illness throughout.
</P>
<P>
His countenance throughout the event was bright as he smiled
while waving to people, according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, the latest issue of the Lagos-based Tell weekly
claimed that Abacha was "very very ill" due to the development of
liver disease he had suffered for about 10 years.
</P>
<P>
It is reported the presidency has said "we deny that this
story is correct."
</P>
<P>
Security men on Wednesday visited the home of Arit Igiebor,
Editor-in-Chief of Tell magazine, in Lagos and arrested his wife
at the absence of the man.
</P>
<P>
The women was released following a brief arrest after the
security men promised to come back for her unless she produced
her husband within 24 hours, according to a statement issued by
the deputy editor-in-chief of the weekly.
</P>
<P>
It insisted that the magazine "has a duty to inform its
readers of the state of the country... if the junta has contrary
information on the state of Abacha's health, then it could
present it to the Nigeria people." 
</P>
