<HEADLINE> Traffic Control System Impored in Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- An advanced traffic control
system, imported from Siemens AG of Germany, has been put into use
in Dalian, a port city of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The 50-million yuan system controls traffic signal lights at
110 locations in the city.
</P>
<P>
Video monitoring devices have been installed at 60 sites to
help report situation on the roads, and automatic cameras have
been installed at some crossroads to help record traffic
violations.
</P>
<P>
The system reportedly has reduced traffic accidents, improved
the passing capacity of motor vehicles at crossings by 20 percent,
and raised the average speed of vehicles by 20 km per hour. 
</P>
