<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heavy Investment for China's Three Gorges Dam Powerlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China will spend 50 billion
yuan (6 US dollars) on power transmission lines for the gigantic
dam at the Three Gorges on the middle reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used for 9,100 km of 500 kilovolt power
lines.
</P>
<P>
The amount of funding needed for power transmission equipment
was calculated at 27.5 billion yuan, at May 1993 levels, while the
amount for the dam itself was estimated at 90 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Actual spending on the Three Gorges Dam will exceed 200 billion
yuan if price increases and interest on loans are taken into
account.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Dam is expected to prevent flooding on the
Yangtze and to have an annual power output of 84.7 billion
kwh. The entire project will take 17 years to complete.
</P>
<P>
The first group of generators will begin generating power in
2003. Power from the dam will mainly be transmitted to central and
east China, with a portion of it going to eastern
parts of neighboring Chongqing, which became a municipality last
March.
</P>
<P>
The China National Power Grid Construction Co. Ltd. is in
charge of the investment, construction and management of the power
transmission lines, which are being built at the same time as the
dam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
