<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Meeting of Party Congress Presidium Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The first meeting of the
presidium of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) was held at the Great Hall of the People here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Jiang Zemin attended the meeting and delivered an
important speech.
</P>
<P>
The standing committee of the presidium, which consisted of
Jiang Zemin and other 32 members, was approved by a show of hands
at the meeting which was presided over by Hu Jintao,
secretary-general of the congress.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, all the items on the agenda were adopted at the
meeting presided over by Jiang Zemin. And at the meeting, Ding
Guangen, Wen Jiabao and Zeng Qinghong were approved as deputy
secretaries-general of the congress by a show of hands.
</P>
<P>
All attending heard a report on the examination of all the
delegates' qualification by the credentials committee.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the Party Central Committee decided
that the number of delegates to the congress be 2050. Of them,
2049 delegates were to be elected from the electoral units. One
of the delegates was then suggested by its electoral unit to have
his delegate's qualifications rescinded, owing to his serious
mistakes. The actual number of delegates now is 2048.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the elections of the delegates had been
conducted by following the principle of democratic centralism and
giving full play to inner-Party democracy. The overall election was
carried out smoothly, it said.
</P>
<P>
All steps of recommendation and election in all electoral units
were carried out in strict accordance with the procedures
determined by the Party Central Commitee, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Over 95 percent of the grassroots Party organizations, and over
85 percent of the Party members took part in the election. All
electoral units conducted serious investigations about the
political qualifications, ethics, work achievements and honest and
clean work style of the delegates, it added.
</P>
<P>
The delegates elected are advanced and highly representative,
the report said, stressing that they firmly believe in communism.
They have earnstly studied Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and have been resolutely
carrying out the basic line of the Party, and all have made
outstanding contributions to the country's reforms, opening-up and
socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the credentials committee as saying that the
election of all 2,048 delegates to the current congress conforms
to the relevant procedures determined by the Party Central
Committee, hence the qualifications of the delegates are valid.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the 14th National Party Congress, the Party
Central Committee specially invited 60 delegates to the current
congress, and they enjoy equal rights as the elected delegates.
</P>
<P>
The draft electoral method of the congress was approved at the
meeting and was then handed over to each delegation for
deliberations.
</P>
<P>
Items concerning the attending of observers and guests at the
congress were also approved at the meeting. The Party Central
Committee decided to invite relevant leading Party officials, as
well as a group of non-Party public figures to attend the congress
as non-voting participants.
</P>
<P>
These non-voting participants, totaling 296 in number, include
non-delegate members and alternate members of the 14th CPC Central
Committee, members of the Central Commission for Discipline
Inspection, non-delegate nor specially invited delegates but
former members of the Central Advisory Commission and some Party
veterans.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a number of 140 non-Party guests were also invited
as observors to attend the opening and closing sessions of the
congress, and they include state vice-president, vice-chairmen of
the Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC)
and the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), leading members of the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce and all non-communist parties,
and figures without party affiliations, non-Party members of the
NPC Standing Committee and the CPPCC National Committee who are
now in Beijing, as well as representatives of ethnic minorities
and the religious circle.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the congress was approved by the presidium
meeting. According to the agenda, the 15th CPC National Congress
is to declare open tomorrow morning, and close on the afternoon of
September 18.  
</P>
</TEXT>
