<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Relations With African Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- For several decades,
relations between China and African countries have been based on
equality and mutual respect and China is a good friend of theirs,
Nigeria's ambassador to China, Zubair Mahmud Kazaure, told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He said that China attaches great importance to Sino-African
ties, as seen in visits by President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng,
Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, and Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen in recent years that have improved the traditional
friendship.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council,
China plays an important role in world affairs, but has never
tried to put pressure on other countries, Kazaure said.
</P>
<P>
The reason Sino-African friendships have withstood the test of
time is that China and the African states, as developing
countries, have similar histories of invasion and being bullied by
colonialists, and they now face the same task of developing their
economies and improving the living standard of their people,
Kazaure said.
</P>
<P>
China and African countries have always supported each other
and it has aided Nigeria and other African countries politically
and economically, and aid to African countries has become more
effective in economic development.
</P>
<P>
Kazaure has visited many places in China and has been impressed
with China's economic development marked by a high rate of growth,
and low inflation. Nigeria's economic exchanges with Shanghai,
Dalian and Qingdao have been increasing.
</P>
<P>
He has also visited Gansu Province, where dry-farming methods
are used. He said that the methods seem applicable to Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
He said the the "China threat theory" is baseless and noted
that China is an influential country but one that has never used
hegemony and power politics, but has always emphasized that
international conflicts should be settled through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
The fact that China resumed the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong is an example of China's not being aggressive, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He added that Nigeria hopes to see China's reunification at an
early date and that Nigeria and other African countries would like
to co-operate with a China that is becoming increasingly strong.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
