<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Specialists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, is home to more than 500,000
specialists with graduate degrees of specialized technological
qualifications.
</P>
<P>
Said individuals account for nearly 10 percent of the city
population.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has introduced various methods in recent years to
train or recruit more qualified personnel to fulfill the demands
of rapid economic development.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has established a number of new universities to serve
as bases for specialized training, including Guangdong
Polytechnics University, Guangzhou Foreign Studies and Trade
University and the Southern China Institute of Science and
Engineering.
</P>
<P>
City colleges such as the Guangzhou Teachers College and
Southern China Construction College are also forging ahead,
according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
The Guangdong Provincial and Guangzhou Municipal government
have extended great effort to attract qualified persons,
especially for the hi-tech sector. Two academicians from the
Chinese Academy of Sciences and a number of people with doctorate
degrees have moved to the city over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Some 9,267 advanced specialists and technicians worked for
government departments and state-run enterprises in Guangzhou in
1996, up 73.9 percent compared with 1990.  
</P>
</TEXT>
