<HEADLINE> Souvenir Book on HKSAR Establishment Goes on Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- An official souvenir book
which contains more than 200 photographs capturing the most
momentous moment in Hong Kong's history is now available to the
public.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) is taking copies with him on his
overseas visits as gifts to the world leaders he meets, according
to the Government Information Services Department.
</P>
<P>
Taken by the department's photographers, the collection
provides a unique view of those never-to-be-forgotten events
centered around midnight on June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The 117-page book, entitled "Entering a New Era", covers the
handover ceremony, the inauguration ceremony of the HKSAR, the
fireworks and laser display and a host of other festivities held
on and after July 1 to celebrate the establishment of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The bilingual text includes the speeches and comments by
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and the chief executive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
