<HEADLINE> Company Wins Contract to Manage HK Parking Spaces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Parking
Ltd. announced here today that it has been awarded a four-year
contract by the government to operate some 14,000 metered parking
spaces throughout Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The contract, which begins on September 20, includes all
metered parking spaces on Hong Kong's streets.
</P>
<P>
The company will be responsible for collecting revenue from the
parking meters, providing necessary civil works and maintaining
and repairing all equipment related to the parking system.
</P>
<P>
The 50-50 joint venture between Serco Guardian (F.M.) Ltd. and
Wilson Parking (Holdings) Ltd. will also manage the
smart-card-operated electronic parking meters that are scheduled
to be installed by the government next year, in replace of the
existing mechanical meters.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong government retains control of parking policy,
including parking fees, enforcement action against parking
offenses, and the cleaning and maintenance of parking bays.
</P>
</TEXT>
