<HEADLINE> Party Congress to Last Seven Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), which opens tomorrow morning
in Beijing, is scheduled to last a week, a congress spokesman
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference in the Great Hall of the People today, Xu
Guangchun, a spokesman of the 15th national Party congress, said
that the congress will last seven days, from September 12 to 18.
</P>
<P>
"The 15th Party congress is a meeting of great significance
convened in the new period when China has scored great
achievements in the reform, opening up and modernization drive,"
Xu told over 600 Chinese and foreign reporters.
</P>
<P>
He said that the congress is a historic meeting held at the
turn of the century when the Party Central Committee with Jiang
Zemin at the core is holding high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics and leading the Chinese people of all ethnic
groups in an all-round advancement of the great cause of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"It is a meeting which summarizes the past and prepares for the
future," he noted. "It ensures that the Party will carry out
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's behests and march unswervingly and
triumphantly along the correct line adopted since the Third Plenum
of the 11th Party Central Committee."
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the congress would uphold Deng
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, review the Chinese people's struggles over the
past century, look ahead at the prospects of China's development
in the first half of the next century, and conscientiously sum up
the experience gained since the Third Plenum of the 11th Party
Central Committee, especially during the past five years following
the 14th national Party congress.
</P>
<P>
"It will lay out a strategic plan for the cross-century
development of our country's reform, opening up and modernization
drive, and mobilize the whole Party and Chinese people of all
ethnic groups to emancipate their minds, seize the favorable
opportunities, and continue to forge ahead in the pioneering
spirit for an all-round advancement of the cause of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics to the 21st century," he
added.
</P>
<P>
He described the congress as "a major event in the political
life of the whole Party and the whole country" that will attract
attention world-wide, saying that the meeting would certainly have
a significant and far-reaching impact on China's future
development.
</P>
<P>
He then made a brief introduction of the agenda of the 15th CPC
National Congress, as well as the congress' preparatory meeting
and the first meeting of the presidium convened this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He also revealed that after the First Plenum of the 15th Party
Central Committee, which is scheduled to follow the congress,
members of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the
new CPC Central Committee would have a meeting with foreign and
Chinese reporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
