<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Become First Rich Country in SA: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's Economic
development will outstrip Indian and Pakistan by the first decade
of the coming century, official news agency Bangladesh Sangbad
Sangstha (BSS) today quoted a Pakistan economist as saying.
</P>
<P>
This statement was made at a seminar on Human Resources
Development in South Asia at Ottawa, Canada, on September 8, by
Dr. Mahbulbul Haq, eminent economist and former finance and
planning minister of Pakistan, who also held high positions in the
World Bank, IMF and UNDP.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Haq commented that Bangladesh has already progressed
substantially in the women education and job sectors and the
NGO's and the social organizations, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
He observed that Bangladesh has already reduced its dependence
on foreign aid and has increased its export trade through
industrialization.
</P>
<P>
"the country which was known for its natural disasters, now
seems to be full of natural resources," Dr. Haq remarked.
</P>
<P>
In this context, Dr. Haq mentioned that world's largest gas
reserves are found in the sea shores of Bangladesh. "it is
expected that Bangladesh will soon become the first rich country
in South Asia," Dr. Haq added. 
</P>
