<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meeting of 15th CPC National Congress Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The preparatory meeting of
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
was held at the Great Hall of the People here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Jiang Zemin presided over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,048 delegates to the congress were elected from 36
electoral units. With 60 delegates specially invited by the Party
Central Committee, the total number of delegates is 2,108.
</P>
<P>
Attending the preparatory meeting today were 2,041 delegates of
the 15th National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
A 19-member credentials committee was approved by a show of
hands at the meeting. A presidium of the congress consisting
of 217 members was approved. Hu Jintao was approved as the
secretary-general of the congress. Those attending the meeting
also approved the tasks of the secretariat of the congress and its
organizational setup.
</P>
<P>
The following agenda for the 15th National Party Congress was
also adopted at the meeting:
</P>
<P>
-- Hear and examine the report of the 14th Party Central
Committee;
</P>
<P>
-- Examine the (written) work report of the Central Commission
for Discipline Inspection;
</P>
<P>
-- Deliberate and approve "An Amendment to the Constitution of
the Communist Party of China;
</P>
<P>
-- Elect a new CPC Central Committee;
</P>
<P>
-- Elect a new Central Commission for Discipline Inspection.
</P>
