<HEADLINE> Guangdong Forestry Attracts Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Forestry Department in
south China's Guangdong Province, a pioneering province in the
nation's opening and moderization drive, has attracted 950 million
US dollars foreign investment in recent years, with 104 million
already used.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, which neighbors Hong Kong and Macao, has 9.13
million ha of forests, with a forest coverage rate of 56.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province's afforestation achievements and preferential
policies have prompted a number of major overseas companies to
invest in the local forestry industry.
</P>
<P>
Various overseas companies have provided loans, with others
participating in cooperative projects, and still others
establishing solely foreign-funded ventures. The province has also
absorbed foreign government loans and donations for forestry
development.
</P>
<P>
Foreign funding is earmarked for the development of
rapid-growth trees, fruit trees, timber processing ventures,
papermaking and institutions for scientific forestry research.
</P>
<P>
Six foreign companies had provided direct investments for
afforestation by the end of last year, with related projects
covering over 240,000 hectares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
