<HEADLINE> Siemens Increases Investment in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Siemens plans to further
increase its investment in southwest China's Sichuan Province and
strengthen its cooperation with local partners.
</P>
<P>
Hermann Koelle, managing director of Siemens (China) noted the
vast potential Sichuan can offer in terms of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Koelle attributed Sichuan's importance for Siemens to the
province's comprehensive industrial system which covers areas such
as energy, metallurgy, mining, chemicals, machine-building, space
technology and electronics, as well as the fact that it is one of
the nation's priority areas for infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
Siemens Chengdu Optical Cable Co. leads the nation with an
annual cable production capacity of 400,000 km. In addition, the
Siemens office in the capital city of Chengdu has earned profits
of 23 million US dollars over the past two years from sales of
telecommunications, medical equipment, industrial automation,
computers and various other ventures.
</P>
<P>
The cable company, established in November 1994 by Siemens
(China) and a local electric cable producer, will have an annual
cable production capacity of one million km following the
completion of second phase construction.
</P>
<P>
The completion of third phase construction will raise the
capacity even further to two million km.
</P>
<P>
Koelle said that Siemens plans to establish additional joint
ventures in Sichuan, including an interface network production
company in Chengdu's Hi-Tech Development Zone. Koelle said the
plant would be established with an initial investment of 30
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
He added that Siemens has also formed a hydropower department
in the Chengdu Office to focus on preparations for establishing a
joint venture hydropower equipment production company.  
</P>
</TEXT>
