<P>
During his three-day visit to Russia, Ramos will meet his
Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin and other senior government
officials.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, who will return home on September 20, will travel on to
Kuwait, the Czech Republic and Austria after his stay in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, accompanied by a large group of prominent businessmen,
will address these countries' businessmen in order to draw
investments to the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Several bilateral agreements and private joint venture
agreements are expected to be signed during the trip.  
</P>
</TEXT>
