<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, September 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Republic of Georgia and its autonomous Republic
of Abkhazia are expected to sign a joint memorandum on the
complete resolution of conflicts between the two sides, in Moscow
soon, according to a joint communique issued Wednesday after
two-day talks held in the Abkhazian capital of Sukhumi.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Itar-Tass news agency and Interfax said the two
sides mainly discussed issues of refugee repatriation and joint
efforts to fight terrorism in warring territories. Delegates from
the United Nations and Russia also attended the talks.
(Georgia-Abkhazia-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Panama decided recently to set up an agency to
deal with maritime and fishery matters at the end of an
international conference on the Panama Canal.
</P>
<P>
In its 21st century-oriented shipping plan, Panama also decided
to develop new infrastructure -- inter-oceanic ports and railroads
-- to make itself a center of multi-model transportation.
(Panama-Canal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Momcilo Krajisnik, Serb member of the Bosnian
Presidency, said Wednesday that his recent talk with Bosnian Serb
President Biljana Plavsic yielded no positive results on resolving
the current political crisis, the Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During a four-hour secret meeting held Tuesday in Banja Luka,
Krajisnik suggested that Plavsic reverse "all illegal decisions"
and call the Bosnian Serb parliamentary and presidential elections
at the same time. Plavsic rejected the suggestion.
(Bosnia-Talks-Failure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The best way for the United States to help Hong
Kong is to develop good relations with China, Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, said
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Tung implied that it was wrong for some
United States congressmen to propose bills on elections in Hong
Kong. He advised: "The best way for America to help Hong Kong is
really to improve its relationship with China. (U.S.-Tung-Visit)
