<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Merger Produces World's Largest Skate Manufacturer in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A skate producer in Qiqihar in
China's northernmost Heilongjiang province recently became the
world's largest producer of ice sporting goods after it merged
more than 30 outmoded state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The merger has put idle state assets to work and helped expand
production capacity of the Heilong Group. With total assets of 1.3
billion yuan, it now has 60 percent of the world's figure skate
market and 80 percent of hockey skate market.
</P>
<P>
Heilong can produce 1.5 million pairs of skates per year,
compared to 160,000 in the past, and 90 percent of its sports
equipment is exported to markets in many countries, including
Japan, Canada, Germany, the Netherlands, and Romania.
</P>
<P>
While honing its competitive edge in the international sporting
goods market, Heilong is expanding into other sectors like
packaging, pharmaceuticals, and paper making, the manager said.
</P>
<P>
This year, the group acquired the Qiqihar Paper Mill, with
assets valued at 500 million yuan, and intends to improve the
mill's technological level. The mill is expected to increase
production value by 600 million yuan each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
