<HEADLINE> Mongolia, Malaysia to Promote Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Malaysian Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohamad said that his country is willing to
further develop relations with Mongolia, especially in the fields
of trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir, who is on a four-day visit here starting September 8,
made the remarks at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Mahathir, Mongolian Prime Minister
Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan said that his country hoped to develop
cooperation with Malaysia in the fields of politics, economy,
trade, technology, culture, education and defense.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia welcomed Malaysian businessmen to invest in the
country and hoped Malaysia to help Mongolia enter the Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) and participate in the regional
meetings of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN),
said Enkhsaikhan.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said that Malaysia is willing to develop cooperation
in civil aviation with Mongolia and his country's businessmen are
studying the possibility to invest in Mongolia's such sectors as
tourism, transportation, post and telecommunications, mining and
real estate.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Mahathir also met with Mongolian President
Nachagyn Bagabandy and Chairman of the Great Hural (parliament)
Radnasumberlyn Gonchigdorzh, and the two sides signed three
memorandums of cooperation on economy, technology, culture and
education, and civil aviation.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia and Malaysia formally established diplomatic relations
in 1971 and began trading with each other in 1994, which brought
the volume to a total of 1.33 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
