<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay Qualifies for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay finally earned
a berth in the World Cup finals after a 2-1 victory over Bolivia
at Asuncion, Paraguay, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay launched attacks from the beginning of the match and
totally dominated the match. But a tight and effective Bolivian
defense allowed few shots at the goal and goal-keeper Carlos
Trucco also put up several superb saves.
</P>
<P>
But Paraguay finally broke the deadlock at the 27th minute when
goal-keeper Jose Chilavert sent a long pass to Richart Baez, who
headed the ball into the area for Miguel Benitez to score.
</P>
<P>
Nine mintues later, Carlos Gamarra made it 2-0 with a header
from a pass by Francisco Arce.
</P>
<P>
In the second half Bolivian substitute Ramiro Castillo sent a
pass to another second-half substitute Berthy Suarez who made no
mistake in scoring.
</P>
<P>
With the 2-1 win over Bolivia, Paraguay is now 8-2-4 with 26
points and qualified for the World Cup finals for the first time
since 1986. 
</P>
</TEXT>
