<HEADLINE> Peru Beats Uruguay 2-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Peru came from behind to beat
Uruguay in a World Cup soccer qualifying game on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Alvaro Recoba opened the scoring for Uruguay at the 44th minute
with a left-footed shot past Peruvian goaltender Julio Cesar
Balerio.
</P>
<P>
Peru made it one-all at the 57th minute when Roberto Palacios
scored from outside the penalty area past Uruguayan goalkeeper
Robert Siboldi.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, German Carty scored the winner which put
Peru in the fourth and final qualifying spot in their division and
virtually eliminated Uruguay from the hunt for a spot in the World
Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Peru's next game is on the road against Chile on October 12.
