<HEADLINE> Over 100 Arrested for Dynamite Fishing in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian police has
arrested 102 suspects and impounded seven tons of fish in Dar Es
Salaam, coast and Tanga regions since the campaign against
dynamite fishing was launched on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Aden Mwamunyange, Chief Public Relations Officer of the
police, told the local Daily News that gear suspected to have
been used in the illegal fishing, including 45 gas cylinders,
three outboard engine boats and 10 canoes, were confiscated in
the campaign mounted by the police and the Tanzania People's
Defense Force.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were later brought before the court to answer
charges of fishing illegally. They were variably fined or
imprisoned.
</P>
<P>
The joint operation has substantially checked the use of
explosives and pesticides in fishing along the counrtry's coastal
regions at first and later it extended to Lake Tanganyika.
</P>
