<HEADLINE> Colombia Beats Venezuela to Qualify for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Colombia beat Venezuela 1-0 in
a World Cup qualifying match at Barranquilla on Wednesday and
snatched a berth in next year's World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian team had a slow start but soon dominated the
match thanks to creative passing and good penetration on the right
side by Asprilla and Antony de Avila.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela also had several scoring opportunities in the first
half but was totally overwhelmed by the host team in the second
half.
</P>
<P>
Defender Wilmer Cabrera headed in the winner at the 67th minute
after taking a chip from star forward Faustino Asprilla.
</P>
<P>
The victory put Colombia in the second place behind Argentina
with 27 points. Top four teams of the South American qualifying
tournament qualify for the World Cup finals.

