<HEADLINE> Belgium Becoming Top Investor In Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Belgium is becoming the top
investor in Bulgaria, as a Belgian company concluded a deal
Wednesday with the Bulgarian Ownership Office to buy 65 percent
shares of Pirdop, the Bulgarian copper complex.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene joined his
Bulgarian counterpart Ivan Kostov in the signing ceremony of the
contract, which was worth 80 million U.S. dollars, the Bulgarian
Telegraph Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The deal pushed Belgium's total investment in Bulgaria to 250
million dollars, making Belgium replace Germany to be Bulgaria's
biggest foreign investor.
</P>
<P>
under the contract, Belgium will invest 220 million dollars
more in Pirdop in the next four years. Belgium will equip Pirdop
with an electric coppermaking furnace with an annual output of
120,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
