<HEADLINE> Chinese Divers Win 1-meter Springboard Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 10 (Xinhua) -- China won both the men's
and women's 1-meter springboard titles at the FINA Diving World
Cup here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Liu Ben, silver medalist at last World Cup in 1995, totalled
391.20 points for the men's title.
</P>
<P>
Troy Dumais of the United States finished second at 385.77,
followed by Zhou Yilin of China in the third place with a total of
385.62.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jing of China won the women's title of the 1-meter
springboard with 281.55 points.
</P>
<P>
Tan Shuping, who took part in the 1992 and 1996 Olympic Games
but failed to win any medal, finished second with 267.45.
</P>
<P>
Dorte Lindner of Germany, who sustained a nose injury on her
second dive, won the bronze medal with 265.98 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
