<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Helps Northeast China Ease Grain Storage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
since the end of last year provided a discounted loan of 950
million yuan (114 million US dollars) to help northeast China ease
the grain-storage problem.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning, Jilin, and Helongjiang provinces and the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region are the country's major grain
producers, and several years of good harvests have effected a
bottleneck in the local grain storage.
</P>
<P>
The region now has 55.2 billion kg of grain stockpiled, but the
maximum grain storage capacity is only 53 billion kg. And some 42
billion kg of newly harvested grain this year also need storage
space.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Internal Trade Chen Bangzhu said recently at a
meeting on matter that the special loan provided by the central
government is expected to increase the storage capacity for 1.5
billion kg of grain.
</P>
<P>
Of the total discounted loans of 2.35 billion yuan (283 million
US dollars) provided nationwide in the past year, 40 percent have
been used for building low-cost storage depots or for renovating
old granaries in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
