<HEADLINE> Shanghai Develops Environmentally-Friendly Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has set a goal to
build its environmental protection industry into a leading local
sector as part of a strategy for ensuring sustained economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
Local experts point to the promising future for
environmentally-friendly industries which provide capital,
equipment and technology for resolving environmental problems.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai intends to generate annual output of 20 billion yuan
from environment-friendly products by the year 2000, and the
sector is expected to witness an annual growth rate of 25 percent
in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The city will focus on the development of a series of products
and technology related dust removal, desulphurization of power
plant emissions, purification of automobile exhaust fumes,
insulation and sound-proof building materials, the treatment of
waste materials, water and gas, and environmental monitoring
equipment.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai plans to establish between five and ten enterprises
with annual output values of over 100 million yuan each in the
sector by the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
The city will introduce transformations and shift a number of
local state enterprises to the environmental protection sector,
especially enterprises in the fields of machinery and electronics,
metallurgy, building materials and chemicals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
