<HEADLINE> August Railway Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Trains carried a daily
average of 75,000 carloads in August, a year-on-year rise of 1,400
cars.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Railways reports that the transport of key
materials, such as coal, grain, chemical fertilizer, cotton, and
oil surpassed original targets.
</P>
<P>
The results were achieved despite harsh weather conditions in
August, a month in which most parts of China were hit by high
temperatures, while southern parts of the country and some coastal
areas were hit with frequent typhoons and other areas suffered
from heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
Railway departments placed priority on transporting emergency
and disaster relief materials, according to the Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that railways carried more than 2.6 million
passengers last month, including 689,000 long-distance travelers.
</P>
</TEXT>
