<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan New Factory Provides 3,000 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's biggest garment
factory at Kekenadura in Matara District will help relieve the
region's unemployment pressure by providing 3,000 new jobs for
local people.
</P>
<P>
President Chandrika Kumaratunga will inaugurate the factory
later this month.
</P>
<P>
The factory, owned by Tri Star Apparels (Private) Ltd., is to
produce high quality garments for Western buyers.
</P>
<P>
Tri Star already supplies garments to Britain, the United
States and Germany.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to create more jobs, the Local government is
trying to install or build as many as possible telephones,
highways and other infrastructure facilities to attract foreign or
local investment.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show there are 47,000 unemployed youths
in Matara District, Southern Province. The district has a
population of 644,000.  
</P>
