<HEADLINE> Colombian Shrimp Industry Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's
long-depressed shrimp industry has begun to recover this year with
the expectation of 42 million U.S. dollars worth of shrimp exports.
</P>
<P>
The 4,000 hectares of cultivated areas for raising shrimps are
fully operational and forecasts of shrimp exports for 1998 are
optimistically set at 50 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The best year for the Colombian shrimp industry was 1994 when
the output reached 9,500 tons and exports rose to 54 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The industry shrank in 1995 and 1996 because of a shrimp
mortality rate of between 70 and 92 percent. In 1995, the output
dropped to only 1,500 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
