<HEADLINE> Italian Minister Confident of 1.2 Percent Annual Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Italian Treasury and Budget
Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi said in Bologma today that he was
confident that the Italian economy will grow by 1.2 percent this
year.
</P>
<P>
Citing similar figures in an International Monetary Fund (IMF)
report, Ciampi said "even those who gave us less than 1.2 percent
today agree that this result is possible."
</P>
<P>
"The economy is doing well," he said. "Making a comparison with
the situation of one ago, the entire picture has improved, has
almost been overturned, with a lower rate of inflation, a balance
of payments which is very strong and a recovery in industrial
production." 
</P>
