<HEADLINE> Africa Woos Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The South African
Development Community (SADC) is looking forward to enhancing its
economic and trading ties with the Southern Common Market
(Mercosur), said South Africa's Vice President Thambo Mbeki.
</P>
<P>
Both blocs are not at present considering signing trade
agreements, but they are willing to exchange their experience,
Mbeki said today in an interview with the Brazilian press.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki said South Africa supports Brazil's effort to be a
permanent member of the United Nations Security Council.
</P>
<P>
He met with Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso and
Foreign Minister Luiz Felipe Lampreia today.
</P>
<P>
The SADC groups 14 African countries, while Mercosur's members
are Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, with Chile and
Bolivia being associate countries. 
</P>
