<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Small Book Found in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A 100-year-old book with the
size of an envelope was recently discovered in east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Each page of the book contains 3,200 Chinese characters, with
each character occupying 0.2 square centimeters.
</P>
<P>
The book records an essay by Confucius, a great Chinese
philosopher who lived over 2,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The handwritten work was completed in the late Qing Dynasty
(1644-1911) by an unknown calligrapher. Experts note that the book
is of significance for the study of ancient publications and
calligraphy
</P>
<P>
The book might be a product for examineers to carry to public
servant examination places to make fraud at that time, experts
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
