<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Car Imports Drop in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Thailand imported a total of
1,251 assembled cars in August this year, 500 units less than it
imported in July.
</P>
<P>
Among the cars, 739 units were imported from the United States,
while 289 were from Europe and 220 from Japan, according to
statistics by the Thai Customs Department available today.
</P>
<P>
U.S. car manufacturer Chrysler had the lion's share of the
imports, totaling 627 units, followed by Volkswagen with 119
units, Ford with 112, and Nissan with 100.  
</P>
</TEXT>
