<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Language School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Coastal
International Language School jointly established by China and
Japan will welcome its first class of students on September 15.
</P>
<P>
The school was jointly established by the Tanggu Workers
College in Tianjin and the Tokyo East Sea College of Japan.
</P>
<P>
One of the school's major goals is to train a large number of
people with a good command of the Japanese language for joint
ventures, foreign-funded enterprises, and city departments dealing
in foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
The school will also provide highly skilled graduates for
Japanese corporations and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Students attending the school study the Japanese language under
the direction of native speakers.  
</P>
