<DOCNO> XIE19970911.0288 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0200 GMT, September 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordan said Wednesday the reason for arresting the
Amman-based Hamas spokesman is that he had made statements
undermining the Kingdoms national security.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Jordan has made public the charge on
Ibrahim Ghosheh who was arrested on Sunday. (Jordan-Hamas)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Meeting with United States Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright late Wednesday, Israeli opposition Labor party
leader Ehud Barak warned that the current crisis in the
Israeli-Arab peace process could lead to war.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference held after his 50-minute meeting
with Albright, Barak said that the meeting focused on the issue of
fighting terrorism. (Israel-Albright-Opposition Meeting)
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The State Department on Wednesday called Beijing
Talks between the United States and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) "useful and productive."
</P>
<P>
"Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Charles Kartman met North
Korea Vice Foreign Minister Kim Gye-gwan today (Wednesday) in
Beijing. The meeting was useful and productive. It was conducted
in a professional manner," spokesman James Foley told
reporters. "They will meet again tomorrow to continue their
discussion." (US-DPRK-Talks)
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Senate Armed Services Committee
Wednesday unanimously recommended that the Senate confirm Army
Gen. Henry Shelton as Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff of the
U.S. military.
</P>
<P>
The Committee's support for the current commander of America's
elite special operations troops came a day after he testified on
his nomination by President Bill Clinton to replace Army Gen. John
Shalikashvili, who is to retire by the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
The Senate vote is expected to be held on
Thursday. (US-Military-Nomination)
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl Wednesday said he was
optimistic that the planned single European currency, the Euro,
would be introduced punctually on January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a parliament debate on Wednesday, Kohl stressed
that his government would do its best to ensure that the Euro
would be launched at the agreed time and be a stable currency in
the long run. (Germany-Euro)
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Austria is pledging to help Ukraine with its pursuit of
European Union (EU) membership, visiting Austrian Vice Chancellor
and Foreign Minister Wolfgang Schussel said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Schussel made the comment as the two countries plan to broaden
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Ukraine is widely viewed as a potent stabilizing factor in
Europe," said Schussel, who arrived here Wednesday on a one-day
working trip. "So Austria will keep supporting Ukraine's
integration with Europe." (Ukraine-Austria-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
