<HEADLINE> Information Industry Strengthened in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Changsha, capital of central
China's Hunan Province, recently started speeding up development
of its information industry.
</P>
<P>
Project 2000 Changsha Information is expected to help the
information industry account for more than half the city's GNP and
a third of the city's labor force by 2015, according to a city
government official.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to assist in building information network
platforms that connect government offices, enterprises, institutes
of higher learning, and research institutes, and other networks at
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 200 research centers and
technology-intensive enterprises in Changsha, including a large
computer base, which are involved in research and development in
the information industry. 
</P>
