<HEADLINE> Guangdong Opens Largest Textile Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province recently opened its largest textile market which focuses
on trade transactions of cloth and wollens.
</P>
<P>
The Tianxiong market, established with a total investment of
over 30 million yuan (3.6 million U.S. dollars) has attracted 300
domestic state-owned textile enterprises and more than 150 textile
producers from overseas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The market provides comprehensive services, including finance,
insurance, taxation and cargo transport. The market's information
center will issue timely releases concerning the latest demand on
cloth and wollens of those ready-to-wear clothing markets in
Taiwan, Japan, the Republic of Korea and Southeast Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 stores and shops have been ready for
operation which covers an area of 58,000 sq.m., and a wholesale
center covering 350,000 sq.m. is under construction. 
