<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt, Ghana, Argentina Reach Last Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Egypt booked a quarter-final
seat at the Under-17 World Soccer Chmapionship after drawing with
Germany here on Wednesday. Germany remains Group A's top team
with seven points.
</P>
<P>
To the ecstacy of 90,000 Egyptian fans in Cairo Stadium, the
Egyptian junior footballers took the command of the game since the
kickoff and opened the account with a skillful shot by Mohammed
Eid in the penalty area in the 66th minute.
</P>
<P>
Germany, which had already qualified, broke even ten minutes
later with a swift header by Benjamin Auer.
</P>
<P>
Both sides exchanged attacks but failed to turn them into goals
in the remaining time. With five points at hand, Egypt will play
the winner of Group B on Sunday in its first quarter-final clash.
</P>
<P>
If Germany won, Chile would have qualified for the quarter-
finals. Chile defeated Thailand 6-2 Wednesday in Ismailia in
another Group A match, getting four points. Thailand was ousted
after losing three matches.
</P>
<P>
Ghana and Argentina also made it to the last eight of the
championship after beating Costa Rica and Bahrain 2-0 respectively
in the last round of Group D matches played in the Mediterranean
city of Port Said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In Group D's last game played in the Egyptian northern city of
Alexandria, Ghana beat Costa Rica two to love, proving its
potential to dominate the U-17 championship.
</P>
<P>
The strongly-built Ghanaians scored one goal in each of the two
halves, showering the Costa Rican goalkeeper with a barrage of
effective attacks.
</P>
<P>
Coming second to Ghanaians, Argentina beat Bahrain 2-0 in
another Group D match played at Port Said, thus edging the
Bahrainians out of the championship.
</P>
<P>
Oman and Brazil, due to meet Thursday, have qualified
regardless of the result of their game, which will help only
determine their placing in Group C.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the tie on Thursday between the United States and
Austria, both ousted from the competition, will be just for
face-saving.
</P>
<P>
So far, Spain is the only qualifier for the quarter-finals in
Group B. Thursday's match between Mali and Mexicao, who have an
equal 3-point stock, will specify the other Group B qualifier.
</P>
<P>
The Under-17 World Championship started in Egypt on September
4 and will run until September 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
