<HEADLINE> Dow Drops 132 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average slid more than 130 points today as investors continue to
care more about company earnings and inflation.
</P>
<P>
The Dow fell 132.63 points to 7,719.28.
</P>
<P>
Broader measures also fell. Declining issues outnumbered
advancers by more than a 5-to-3 margin on the New York Stock
Exchange, with its volume totaling 516.75 million shares as
against 502.11 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; and Poor's 500-stock list fell 14.59 to 919.03,
and the NYSE composite index fell 6.06 to 480.63.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index, which closed at
record highs the previous three sessions, fell 16.96 to 1,639.26.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 0.85 to
436.90. The index had risen for 12 straight sessions, closing at
record highs in the last nine.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index, which is dominated
by smaller companies, fell 1.16 to 670.27, ending its stretch of
record highs at six sessions.
</P>
<P>
The market has been worrying about third-quarter profits and
inflationary pressures, leading to the downturn of blue-chips.
</P>
